                </note>
                <note type="article">
                    <p xml:id='OTPS53282P0'>Currently located in Copiah County, Gallatin was founded in 1819 in what was then a "non-county area." On February 12, 1821 it was merged into Hinds County until January 21, 1823, when Gallatin became part of the newly founded Copiah County. It was incorporated in 1829 and served as the county seat until 1872 (when it was replaced by Hazlehurst). Presently, Gallatin is a deserted town with few or no remaining inhabitants. (Rowland, <hi rend='italic'>Mississippi</hi>, 758; Wikipedia)
</p>


                </note>
                <note type="geography">
                  <geo>31.865, -90.39139</geo>
                </note>
            </place>
            <place xml:id="S63019">
              <placeName>Mississippi--Adams County. Natchez</placeName>
                <idno>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natchez,_Mississippi</idno>
                <note type="categorization">
                  Categories:
                    <ab>
                        <ptr ana="#category #root" target="#C2751">Places</ptr> --
                      <ptr ana="#category #leaf" target="#C32001862">Towns &amp; Cities</ptr>
                    </ab>
                </note>
                <note type="article">
                    <p xml:id='OTPS63019P0'>Located in Adams County, Natchez was founded in 1716 under the name Fort Rosalie and was renamed Natchez in 1730. It became part of the newly created Adams County on April 1, 1799. It served as the capital of Mississippi Territory from 1798 until 1802, when it was replaced by Washington. It was reinstated as the capital from 1817 until 1820, when the capital was again replaced by Washington (which was later replaced by the current capital Jackson in 1822). Natchez serves as the county seat. (Wikipedia; Britannica; Mississippi Encyclopedia)
</p>


                </note>
                <note type="geography">
                  <geo>31.55444, -91.3875</geo>
                </note>
            </place>
            <place xml:id="S71872">
              <placeName>Mississippi--Copiah County. Hazlehurst</placeName>
                <idno>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hazlehurst,_Mississippi</idno>
                <note type="categorization">
                  Categories:
                    <ab>
                        <ptr ana="#category #root" target="#C2751">Places</ptr> --
                      <ptr ana="#category #leaf" target="#C32001862">Towns &amp; Cities</ptr>
                    </ab>
                </note>
                <note type="article">
                    <p xml:id='OTPS71872P0'>Located in Copiah County, Hazlehurst was founded as early as November 3, 1865. In April 1872, it replaced Gallatin as the county seat and remains so today. (Wikipedia; Atlas of Historical County Boundaries)
</p>


                </note>
