        <div xml:id="OTP33117363">
        <fw type="pageNum">Letter from W. Peck to Major General D. Reynolds; October 19, 1865</fw>
          <p corresp='TTP33117363P0' xml:id='OTP33117363P0'><rs ref='#S53282'>Gallatin Copiah co Missi</rs><lb/>
Octo 19<add place='above'>th</add> 1865
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33117363P1' xml:id='OTP33117363P1'>Major <rs ref='#S32030382'>Geo D Reynolds</rs><lb/>
Actg Asst Com B. F. <rs ref='#S63019'>Natchez Missi</rs>
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33117363P2' xml:id='OTP33117363P2'>The garrison has been removed from <rs ref='#S71872'>Hazlehurst</rs> leaving me without protection—I was compelled last night to surrender to the <rs ref='#S95578'>Sheriff</rs> &amp; his posse who brought me here <rs ref='#S62954'>in custody</rs>—Anticipating trouble I dispatched to <rs ref='#S51726'>Brookhaven</rs> for protection which was not granted
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33117363P3' xml:id='OTP33117363P3'>Signed <rs ref='#S32050433'>W. Peck</rs><lb/>
Capt &amp; Sub com B F
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33117363P4' xml:id='OTP33117363P4'>Copy 
</p>


            <note resp="#U231087">Written to Major George D. Reynolds, not Major General D. Reynolds. https://repository.duke.edu/dc/broadsides/bdsms21225</note>
        </div>
  </body>
